HEADWORD: Diffusive
<hw>Dif*fu"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>diffusif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the quality of diffusing;
capable of spreading every way by flowing; spreading widely; widely
reaching; copious; diffuse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A plentiful and
<xex>diffusive</xex> perfume.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hare.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diffusively</ent>⟦br⟧
